Appearance-pours dark brown with small, quickly dissipating head. 
Nose- bourbon dominates, sweet malt, hint of roast coffee.
Taste-surprisingly heavy chocolate.  Barely any bourbon in taste.  Sweet, chocolate malt.

Truly fantastic.  Part really good wit, part coffee.

Looks hazed gold like a typical Belgian wheat.  Smells just like a cup of good fresh coffee.

Tastes like a good wit with a hint of coffee mixed in.

I really wouldnt have expected this to work, let alone to be so fantastic.

Served in a 7oz flute at jake melnicks in Chicago.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

I get something fruity and something a bit cough syrup.   Can't say its really pleasant.  Surprising since I'm a big fan of rouge hazelnut and coffe porters.

Clear amber color, fruity smell.  Low carb, which could be the bars fault.

As it stands, I wouldnt order again.
